9 An Act relating to agriculture; creating the Advisory
Council on Product Classification; providing
10 membership terms and duties; allowing for
reimbursement of travel expenses under the State
11 Travel Reimbursement Act; providing for codification;
and providing an effective date.
12
13
14 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
15 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
16 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 2-35 of Title 2, unless there is
17 created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
18 A. There is hereby created within the Oklahoma Department of
19 Agriculture, Food, and Forestry, the Advisory Council on Product
20 Classification.
21 B. The Council shall serve solely in an advisory role and shall
22 advise and make recommendations to the Department regarding the
23 classification of agriculture and food products for purposes
24 conducted by the Department.
SB2127 HFLR Page 1
BOLD FACE denotes Committee Amendments.

1 C. The Council shall be composed of five (5) members appointed
2 by the State Board of Agriculture, all of whom shall represent
3 interests affected by product classification. Members appointed to
4 the Council shall serve at the pleasure of the Board. Appointees to
5 the Council shall serve for a term of five (5) years. Members of
6 the Council shall not be compensated for their service but shall
7 qualify for reimbursement for travel expenses under the State Travel
8 Reimbursement Act.
9 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2026.
10
11 COMMITTEE REPORT BY: COMMITTEE ON ENERGY AND NATURAL RESOURCES
OVERSIGHT, dated 04/13/2026 - DO PASS.
